aws::graph::propositions: Mooney M20J Design and Improvement Timeline
Mooney M20J featured a streamlined engine cooling system.
Mooney M20J included landing gear doors that cover the wheel wells.
Mooney M20J had flush airframe access panels.
Mooney M20J incorporated a new exhaust stack.
Mooney M20J utilized flaps with faired-in hinges.
Mooney M20J flaps included gap seals.
Mooney M20J was equipped with a more efficient McCauley propeller.
In 1978, the Mooney M20J engine was replaced with a Lycoming IO-360-A3B6D.
The Lycoming IO-360-A3B6D had similar power to the previous engine in the Mooney M20J.
In 1978, a power quadrant replaced the original push-pull engine controls in the Mooney M20J.
The 1981 model of Mooney M20J introduced redesigned wingtips from the M20K.
The 1981 model of Mooney M20J featured improved soundproofing.
Soundproofing was further improved in the 1982 model of Mooney M20J.
The 1982 model of Mooney M20J added double-pane door windows.
The 1982 model of Mooney M20J included extra stiffeners in the cabin.
The 1982 model of Mooney M20J added extra insulation in the cabin.
The 1984 model of Mooney M20J introduced improved instrument panels.
The 1984 model of Mooney M20J featured improved circuit breaker panels.
The 1984 model of Mooney M20J incorporated a streamlined composite belly panel.
Wing-mounted air brakes were made available as an option for the Mooney M20J in 1985.

text: These changes included a streamlined engine cooling system, landing gear doors that cover the wheel wells, flush airframe access panels, a new exhaust stack, flaps with faired-in hinges and gap seals, and a more efficient McCauley propeller.  In 1978, the engine was swapped for a similarly-powered Lycoming IO-360-A3B6D, and a power quadrant replaced the original push-pull engine controls.  The 1981 model introduced the redesigned wingtips of the M20K to the M20J, as well as improved soundproofing.  Soundproofing was further improved in 1982 with the addition of double-pane door windows as well as extra stiffeners and insulation in the cabin.  The 1984 model introduced improved instrument and circuit breaker panels and a streamlined composite belly panel.  Wing-mounted air brakes were made available as an option in 1985.
